hotspot.description: The ESL Resource Center provides academic assistance and support services for second-language students currently enrolled in college-preparation ESL courses at Rowan College of South Jersey. It also serves second language students who have completed the program, and/or attained college-level proficiency, and are enrolled in college-level courses. Staff provide tutoring and advisement services for the students. The ESL Center also serves as a "cultural hub" for second-language students to gather and share ideas and practice their English skills.

hotspot.description: The Mechatronics Innovation Learning Laboratory (M.I.L.L.) is a newly renovated applied engineering facility designed to provide industry grade equipment, curriculum, technology, and training adapted to employer needs. The goal of this facility is to cater to employer, employee, and student needs by providing flexible hands-on lab hours to both the working and non-working students. The MILL provides access to 5- and 3- axis HAAS CNC machines, FANUC robotics, PLCs, motor controls, conveyor belts and other mechanical, electrical and pneumatic training equipment to prepare students for nationally recognized industry credentials. We offer a variety of workforce development training options for those currently employed, unemployed and those seeking to pivot in engineering technology as technicians, technologists and engineers with practical and relevant industry technology experience.
hotspot.title: Mechatronics Innovation Learning Laboratory (M.I.L.L.)

hotspot.description: The Luciano Conference Center is home to our Business Studies Division. Offerings within the Center also include our spacious Banquet Room for academic lecture halls, as well as campus wide meetings and conferences. Our banquet room provides a versatile space and is fully equipped with up-to-date technology to include overhead projectors, large viewable screens, microphones and wifi.
hotspot.title: Conference Center

hotspot.description: The Frank Guaricini Fine and Performing Arts Center is a single-story building comprising a total conditioned floor area of 42,756 square feet. The original structure was built in 1992, with additions in 2002 and interior renovations in 2008. It houses classrooms, offices, black box studio, a theatre and gallery spaces. The Luciano Theatre in the Frank Guaricini, Jr. Fine and Performing Arts Center, is a 500-seat state of the art theatre and is home to our academic award-winning student productions featuring Broadway caliber plays and musicals as well as concerts by Bay Atlantic Symphony and the Vineland Regional Dance Company. The theatre has a complete fly system, adequate wing space and two adjacent dressing rooms to the stage.
